# SPA (React) routes -> the app shell. Target the EXTENSIONLESS /app, not
# /app.html: Cloudflare Pages' automatic .html clean-URL handling turns a
# rewrite to /app.html into a 308 redirect to /app, which drops the original
# path (e.g. /comp) and lands the SPA on /app with no matching route. Serving
# the clean /app keeps the request URL intact so react-router routes correctly.
# The static content pages (/, /about, /legal, /scoring, /scoring/*) are real
# prerendered files (built by ./static with Astro) and are served directly.
/u/*  /app  200
/comp  /app  200
/comp/*  /app  200
/scores  /app  200
/profile  /app  200
/settings  /app  200
/onboarding  /app  200
/admin/users  /app  200
/admin/cache  /app  200

# Old static-page URLs (linked from bookmarks and the vanilla analysis/replay pages)
/about.html  /about  301
/legal.html  /legal  301
/scoring.html  /scoring  301
/scoring-gap.html  /scoring/gap  301
/scoring-open-distance.html  /scoring/open-distance  301
/theme-editor  /  301
/kitchensink.html  /  301
